# Issue #258 — sh:node must dispatch to the FULL constraint-evaluation logic for
# the referenced inner shape (evaluate.rs::node_conforms_to_inner previously only
# understood sh:class / sh:nodeKind / sh:property[sh:minCount>=1]).
# https://github.com/daghovland/rdf-datalog/issues/258
PREFIX sh: <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#>
PREFIX ex: <http://example.com/ns#>
PREFIX xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#>

ex:NodeDatatypeShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetNode ex:ndDtOk, ex:ndDtBad ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ex:address ;
        sh:node [ sh:property [ sh:path ex:v ; sh:datatype xsd:integer ] ] ;
    ] .

ex:NodePatternShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetNode ex:ndPatOk, ex:ndPatBad ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ex:address ;
        sh:node [ sh:property [ sh:path ex:v ; sh:pattern "^foo" ] ] ;
    ] .

ex:NodeInShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetNode ex:ndInOk, ex:ndInBad ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ex:address ;
        sh:node [ sh:property [ sh:path ex:v ; sh:in ( ex:A ex:B ) ] ] ;
    ] .

ex:NodeHasValueShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetNode ex:ndHvOk, ex:ndHvBad ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ex:address ;
        sh:node [ sh:property [ sh:path ex:v ; sh:hasValue ex:Expected ] ] ;
    ] .

ex:NodeMaxCountShape
    a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetNode ex:ndMcOk, ex:ndMcBad ;
    sh:property [
        sh:path ex:address ;
        sh:node [ sh:property [ sh:path ex:v ; sh:maxCount 1 ] ] ;
    ] .
